The paper deals with the analysis and design of recovery algorithms for compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on node-based verification-based algorithms, which are a type of iterative algorithm commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of irregular graphs in the design of these algorithms, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper uses probabilistic analysis techniques, which are commonly used in statistical inference (cs.SI) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
